    • Enum Constant Detail

      • Lighten

        public static final Blend.Algorithm Lighten
        It selects the maximum of each component from the foreground and background pixels.

      • Darken

        public static final Blend.Algorithm Darken
        Creates a pixel that retains the smallest components of the foreground and background pixels.

      • Multiply

        public static final Blend.Algorithm Multiply
        Simply multiplies each component in the two layers.

      • Average

        public static final Blend.Algorithm Average
        Simply average each component in the two layers.

      • Add

        public static final Blend.Algorithm Add
        This blend mode simply adds pixel values of one layer with the other. In case of values above 1 (in the case of RGB), white is displayed.

      • Subtract

        public static final Blend.Algorithm Subtract
        This blend mode simply subtracts pixel values of one layer with the other. In case of negative values, black is displayed.

      • Difference

        public static final Blend.Algorithm Difference
        Difference subtracts the top layer from the bottom layer or the other way round, to always get a positive value. Blending with black produces no change, as values for all colors are 0. (The RGB value for black is 0,0,0). Blending with white inverts the picture.

      • Negation

        public static final Blend.Algorithm Negation
        Produces the opposite effect to Difference. Instead of making colors darker, it makes them brighter.

      • Screen

        public static final Blend.Algorithm Screen
        The Screen blend mode inverts both layers, multiplies them, and then inverts that result.

      • Exclusion

        public static final Blend.Algorithm Exclusion
        Exclusion blending mode inverts lower layers according to the brightness values in the active layer. White inverts the composite pixels absolutely, black inverts them not at all, and the other brightness values invert them to some degree in between.

      • Overlay

        public static final Blend.Algorithm Overlay
        Overlay combines Multiply and Screen blend modes. The parts of the top layer where base layer is light become lighter, the parts where the base layer is dark become darker. An overlay with the same picture looks like an S-curve.

      • SoftLight

        public static final Blend.Algorithm SoftLight
        This is a softer version of Hard Light. Applying pure black or white does not result in pure black or white.

      • HardLight

        public static final Blend.Algorithm HardLight
        Hard Light combines Multiply and Screen blend modes. Equivalent to Overlay, but with the bottom and top images swapped.

      • ColorDodge

        public static final Blend.Algorithm ColorDodge
        Color Dodge blend mode divides the bottom layer by the inverted top layer.

      • ColorBurn

        public static final Blend.Algorithm ColorBurn
        Color Burn mode divides the inverted bottom layer by the top layer, and then inverts the result.

      • LinearLight

        public static final Blend.Algorithm LinearLight
        Linear Light combines Linear Dodge and Linear Burn (rescaled so that neutral colors become middle gray). Dodge applies to values of top layer lighter than middle gray, and burn to darker values. The calculation simplifies to the sum of bottom layer and twice the top layer, subtract 1. The contrast decreases.

      • VividLight

        public static final Blend.Algorithm VividLight
        Vivid Light combines Color Dodge and Color Burn (rescaled so that neutral colors become middle gray). Dodge applies when values in the top layer are lighter than middle gray, and burn to darker values. The middle gray is the neutral color. When color is lighter than this, this effectively moves the white point of the bottom layer down by twice the difference; when it is darker, the black point is moved up by twice the difference. (The perceived contrast increases.)

      • PinLight

        public static final Blend.Algorithm PinLight
        Pin Light combines lighten and darken modes.

      • Reflect

        public static final Blend.Algorithm Reflect
        Reflect can be used for adding shiny objects or areas of light.

      • Phoenix

        public static final Blend.Algorithm Phoenix
        Phoenix mode.
